outlet: Anytime Fitness Yew Tee Community Club
author: Joshua Ong
text:
Beware of absurd credit card fees if your payment fails. Was charged $15.26 due to a failed payment on my card because it was expired.

1. Anytime Fitness & Ezypay (their merchant processor) stores the expiry date of cards on file - Even so they still attempt to bill customers KNOWLY that the card is expired so they can earn the money on the ‚Äúfailed payment fee‚Äù. I spoke to the Ezypay staff and they claim ‚Äúthey won‚Äôt know the card is expired until they try to bill the card.‚Äù Which is some BS reason. They HAVE the expiry date of card on file and they can easily setup email reminders for customers to update their payment method. Both AF & EzyPay have the CC expiry date on file and don‚Äôt bother to have automated emails to remind members to update the CC on file.

2. They claim is our responsibility to ensure the payment method is valid. Who in the right mind can recall all the cards and expiry dates? Do you recall the expiry date of the last item you bought from the grocery store? Obviously no.

3. I‚Äôve been a paying member of AF for over 3 years. And they don‚Äôt give a damn and refuse to waive the failed payment fee which they knowingly charge. Beware of their unethical practices. Feel free to file a complaint with CASE..

outlet: Anytime Fitness Yew Tee Community Club
author: Cheryl T
text:
Yew tee AF gym may be small, but it has all the necessary equipment for my workouts (Do hope there are more equipments variety though). It's clean, and the machines are well-maintained, although the air conditioning could use regular servicing.

The manager and staff are incredibly friendly, always greeting members with a smile and engaging in conversation, which creates a welcoming, home-like atmosphere. They're also very helpful, offering fitness advice and demonstrating how to use unfamiliar equipment. This support has made my gym experience much more enjoyable and has given me the confidence to try new exercises.

The other gym-goers are just as friendly, often helping me improve my form, teaching new exercises, and even training with me. This sense of community makes the gym experience fun, and I always look forward to going üòö.

Looks as if there is no manager running that gym.
I lived in Melbourne, and I have been with anytime fitness past 3 years for only one reason... that I can use anytime fitness gym facilities overseas. Having to see this kind of gym standard and maintenance, I am quite sure I will terminate my gym membership definitely after this.

I've been a member at Anytime Fitness Yew Tee for 3 years, and it's been an amazing fitness journey.

One of the standout features of Yew Tee Anytime Fitness is their exceptional management team. They are attentive, responsive, and truly care about the members' experience. Any concerns or suggestions are swiftly addressed, creating a sense of trust and transparency.

The gym's atmosphere is motivating and inclusive. It's not just a place to work out; it's a place where you can connect with like-minded individuals who share your passion for health and fitness. The camaraderie among members here is something I haven't experienced in other gyms.

Highly recommended!
